%20of%20a%20broader%20slowdown%20in%20apparel%20and%20housewares%20in%20recent%20years.%3Cp%3EScott%20Olson%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETJ%20Maxx%20parent%20company%20TJX%20operates%20on%20a%20different%20playbook%20from%20most%20retailers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20particular%2C%20the%20CEO%20says%20it%20wants%20to%20give%20shoppers%20a%20%26quot%3Bwow%26quot%3B%20factor%20from%20finding%20incredible%20value.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20part%20of%20a%20larger%20strategy%20that%20could%20help%20the%20company%20do%20well%20%E2%80%94%20even%20in%20chaotic%20times.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20an%20experience%20that%20almost%20anyone%20shopping%20at%20TJ%20Maxx%2C%20Marshalls%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsierra-store-most-interesting-brand-tjx-portfolio-trading-post-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESierra%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20Home%20Goods%20eventually%20has%3A%20you're%20browsing%20items%2C%20see%20a%20price%20tag%2C%20and%20think%2C%20%26quot%3Bthat%20can't%20be%20right.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20you%20know%20it%2C%20you're%20a%20full-blown%20Maxxinista.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20it%20happens%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftjx-ceo-tariffs-creating-textbook-buying-opportunity-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETJX%3C%2Fa%3E%20CEO%20Ernie%20Herrman%20said%20the%20company%20wants%20you%20to%20feel%20a%20little%20suspicious%20when%20you%20encounter%20a%20sharp%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20want%20a%20customer%20to%20actually%20say%2C%20'That%20almost%20feels%20too%20cheap%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20a%20quarterly%20earnings%20call%20Wednesday.%20%26quot%3BOne%20out%20of%20every%2010%20hangers%20I%20want%20a%20customer%20saying%2C%20'Boy%2C%20that%20that%20almost%20feels%20too%20inexpensive%2C'%20strangely%20enough.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20playbook%20has%20been%20working%20for%20the%20company%2C%20which%20reported%20strong%20sales%20and%20traffic%20gains%20at%20its%20family%20of%20brands%20despite%20a%20broader%20slowdown%20in%20apparel%20and%20housewares%20categories%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20a%20bad-weather%20month%20in%20February%2C%20monthly%20visits%20to%20TJ%20Maxx%20and%20Marshalls%20were%20up%20roughly%206%25%20to%208%25%20in%20January%2C%20March%2C%20and%20April%20of%20this%20year%20versus%20last%20year%2C%20according%20to%20foot%20traffic%20data%20from%20Placer.ai.%20Visits%20to%20traditional%20apparel%20stores%20have%20been%20basically%20flat%20or%20down%20for%20the%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlacer.ai%20also%20found%20that%20not%20only%20do%20shoppers%20visit%20more%20often%2C%20they%20spend%20more%20time%20in%20the%20stores%20as%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericans-budget-era-value-retail-walmart-target-tj-maxx-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehunt%20for%20those%20surprising%20deals%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20significant%20part%20of%20this%20success%20may%20stem%20from%20the%20segment's%20inherent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftjx-ceo-homegoods-has-become-a-bit-of-a-cult-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E'treasure-hunt'%20experience%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20off-price%20shopping%20cultivates%20a%20browsing%20mentality%2C%20encouraging%20visitors%20to%20linger%20and%20explore%20the%20constantly%20changing%20inventory%2C%26quot%3B%20Placer.ai's%20Bracha%20Arnold%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20year%20so%20far%2C%20Placer.ai%20found%20TJ%20Maxx%20shoppers%20spent%20an%20average%20of%2040.3%20minutes%20in%20the%20store%2C%20while%20shoppers%20at%20traditional%20apparel%20chains%20averaged%2033.3%20minutes%20%E2%80%94%20a%20difference%20of%20about%2020%25%20more%20time%20spent%20trying%20to%20find%20that%20suspiciously%20good%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20there's%20a%20lot%20more%20to%20the%20equation%20than%20simply%20offering%20low%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BValue%20isn't%20just%20a%20function%20of%20competitive%20prices%2C%26quot%3B%20Global%20Data%20retail%20analyst%20Neil%20Saunders%20said%20in%20a%20note.%20%26quot%3BIt%20also%20comes%20from%20buying%20well%20and%20meeting%20customer%20needs.%20In%20our%20view%2C%20TJX%20merchants%20are%20excellent%20at%20doing%20at%20that%20and%20they%20are%20one%20of%20the%20key%20assets%20that%20will%20propel%20the%20company%20forward.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20earnings%20call%2C%20Herrman%20said%20TJX%20has%20a%20team%20of%20over%201%2C300%20buyers%20who%20have%20relationships%20with%20more%20than%2021%2C000%20vendors%20across%20more%20than%20100%20countries%20around%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20the%20company%20is%20not%20immune%20from%20tariff%20impacts%20(Herrman%20said%20TJX%20directly%20imports%20about%2010%25%20of%20its%20goods)%2C%20much%20of%20its%20sourcing%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftj-maxx-benefits-donald-trump-tariffs-trade-policies-retail-industry-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edownstream%20from%20other%20brands%20and%20retailers%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20will%20likely%20bear%20a%20fair%20amount%20of%20the%20costs%2C%20rather%20than%20TJX%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGlobal%20trade%20chaos%20now%20represents%20a%20key%20opportunity%20for%20TJX%20to%20load%20up%20on%20interesting%20merchandise%2C%20since%20unexpected%20inventory%20surpluses%20are%20where%20off-price%20retail%20shines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJefferies%20retail%20analyst%20Corey%20Tarlowe%20found%20that%20retail%20inventories%20are%20on%20the%20rise%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20two%20years%2C%20reversing%20a%20trend%20of%20leaner%2C%20more%20disciplined%20inventory%20strategies%20in%20the%20post-COVID%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGiven%20these%20trends%2C%20the%20availability%20for%20TJX%20should%20remain%20robust.%20TJX%20management%20noted%20inventory%20availability%20in%20the%20marketplace%20is%20better%20t