a%20US%20District%20Judge%20on%20Friday%20said%20the%20action%20against%20Jenner%20%26amp%3B%20Block%20was%20unconstitutional.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20entire%20order%2C%20which%20revoked%20the%20security%20clearances%20of%20the%20firm's%20attorneys%20and%20required%20a%20review%20of%20its%20government%20contracts%2C%20was%20invalidated%20by%20the%20judge's%20ruling%2C%20representing%20a%20major%20win%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-war-big-law-targets-jenner-block-firm-resists-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EJenner%20%26amp%3B%20Block%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20order%20raises%20constitutional%20eyebrows%20many%20times%20over.%20It%20punishes%20and%20seeks%20to%20silence%20speech%20'at%20the%20very%20center%20of%20the%20First%20Amendment%2C'%26quot%3B%20US%20District%20Judge%20John%20Bates%2C%20of%20the%20District%20Court%20of%20DC%20wrote%20in%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.courtlistener.com%2Frecap%2Fgov.uscourts.dcd.278932%2Fgov.uscourts.dcd.278932.138.0_6.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eruling%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20adding%20that%20Trump's%20order%20did%20so%20%26quot%3Bvia%20the%20most%20'egregious%20form%20of%20content%20discrimination%20%E2%80%94%20viewpoint%20discrimination%2C'%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bin%20an%20unacceptable%20attempt%20to%20'insulate%20the%20Government's%20laws%20from%20judicial%20inquiry.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20Jenner%20%26amp%3B%20Block%20directed%20Business%20Insider%20to%20their%20public%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jennerfirm.com%2F%23statement%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%20following%20the%20ruling%2C%20which%20said%20that%20the%20firm%20is%20%26quot%3Bpleased%20with%20the%20court's%20decision%20to%20decisively%20strike%20down%20an%20unconstitutional%20attack%20on%20our%20clients'%20right%20to%20have%20zealous%2C%20independent%20counsel%20and%20our%20firm's%20right%20to%20represent%20our%20clients%20fully%20and%20without%20compromise.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20decision%20to%20fight%20the%20executive%20order%20in%20court%20is%20rooted%20in%20Jenner%20%26amp%3B%20Block's%20history%20and%20values%3A%20we%20fiercely%20advocate%20for%20our%20clients%20under%20all%20circumstances%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20firm's%20statement%20continued.%20%26quot%3BThis%20ruling%20demonstrates%20the%20importance%20of%20lawyers%20standing%20firm%20on%20behalf%20of%20clients%20and%20for%20the%20law.%20That%20is%20what%20Jenner%20will%20continue%20to%20do%20for%20our%20clients%20%E2%80%94%20paying%20and%20pro%20bono%20%E2%80%94%20as%20we%20look%20to%20put%20this%20matter%20behind%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20the%20White%20House%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20federal%20government%20can%20appeal%20the%20decision%2C%20in%20which%20case%20the%20proceedings%20will%20be%20heard%20in%20the%20court%20of%20appeals.%20Any%20subsequent%20appeal%20would%20be%20heard%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20from%20US%20District%20Judge%20John%20Bates%2C%20an%20appointee%20of%20former%20President%20George%20W.%20Bush%2C%20is%20the%20second%20order%20striking%20down%20an%20executive%20order%20from%20Trump%20targeting%20a%20law%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20month%2C%20another%20judge%20blocked%20an%20order%20targeting%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjudge-blocks-donald-trump-executive-order-big-law-perkins-coie-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPerkins%20Coie%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20ruling%20that%20Trump's%20use%20of%20federal%20power%20%26quot%3Ban%20overt%20attempt%20to%20suppress%20and%20punish%20certain%20viewpoints.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJudges%20have%20also%20temporarily%20paused%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ft